PR 1 — Refactor
Branch: refactor/logger-module
Title: refactor(logger): schema-from-table, explicit identity, distributed log_dataframe
Commit message:

refactor(logger): simplify and align with architect direction

Read log-table schema from the live Delta table instead of hardcoded
per-subclass StructTypes; the table is the runtime contract. Make run
identity explicit — run_id/task_key are passed from job parameters, with
notebook-context fallback and fail-fast when unresolvable. Remove the
per-task RunContext/context.py layer.

Rewrite log_dataframe as a distributed column transform (F.expr/F.lit +
broadcast-join for per-row governance) instead of collect()-to-driver.
No driver row limit; source data never leaves the cluster.

Collapse duplicated argument validation onto resolve_log_column as the
single source of truth; keep only the inline response_id check it can't
cover. Wire registry.to_lookup_rows into governance resolution so the
lookup tuple shape has one definition. Guard bulk `expected` to scalar,
closing the log()/log_dataframe divergence.

Remove context.py, redundant validators, and stale docstrings.

PR description:

## What
Simplification pass on the logger module ahead of pipeline logging.

## Changes
- Schema read from the target Delta table at runtime (load_table_contract);
  removes hardcoded _SCHEMA from EventLogger/ExceptionLogger.
- run_id/task_key passed explicitly from job params; notebook-context
  fallback; construction raises if unresolvable. context.py deleted.
- source_table/target_table/collection_instance_id moved from constructor
  to per-call, supporting multi-step notebooks and per-row values.
- log_dataframe is now a single distributed write (no collect, no 100k cap).
- Validation collapsed onto resolve_log_column; to_lookup_rows wired in;
  scalar-expected guard added.
- __init__.py: context exports removed, examples corrected.

## Caller-facing breaking changes
- for_task(run_id=, task_key=) — collection/source/target now per log call.
- log_dataframe returns None (was a row count); no oversized-input ValueError.
- Blank run_id/task_key raises at construction.

## Verification
- [ ] grep clean: no RunContext/build_run_context/old for_task signature
- [ ] unit suite green (row-limit/buffer-after-df tests removed)
- [ ] events + exceptions log tables exist in target env

## Not included
PipelineLogger (follow-up PR, depends on this).



PR 2 — Pipeline logger
Branch: feat/pipeline-logger (cut from refactor/logger-module)
Title: feat(logger): add PipelineLogger for final run-status records
Commit message:

feat(logger): add PipelineLogger for pipeline_run

Write one final-status row per pipeline/job run to pipeline_run. Caller
owns status and record_count; run_id/job_id/trigger_type/start_time/
parent_run_id fall back to notebook context when not passed.

Composes base_logger helpers rather than extending BaseLogger — single
row, no buffer. run_id validated at construction (fails at for_pipeline,
not inside the caller's except-block log()); status validated at log().
log() is idempotent per instance.

Depends on refactor/logger-module.


PR description:

## What
Adds PipelineLogger — one final-status record per pipeline/job run.

## Depends on
#<PR-1>. Imports clean_string/load_table_contract/get_notebook_run_context/
align_record_to_schema from the refactored base_logger. Merge after PR 1.

## Design
- Composition over inheritance: single-row writer, no buffering needed.
- Intended caller pattern (per architect):
    p = PipelineLogger.for_pipeline(...)
    try:
        ...work...
        p.log(status="SUCCEEDED", record_count=n)
    except Exception:
        p.log(status="FAILED")
        raise
- run_id validated in __init__ so a bad config can't mask the real
  exception in the except-block. status validated at log().

## Verification
- [ ] pipeline_run DDL merged; columns match _build_record; record_count bigint
- [ ] test schema uses LongType for record_count
- [ ] __init__.py exports PipelineLogger

